# Commit messages

Cloud Foundry requires AI disclosure on contributions per [RFC-0047](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/community/blob/2d2df6e9cb3efa7b0729ea011c0f7e4952cca12f/toc/rfc/rfc-0047-ai-disclosures.md).

## Format for all commits

Every commit message must include an AI disclosure token in square brackets:

```text
<message-text> [ai-assisted]
```

or, if not AI-assisted:

```text
<message-text> [no-ai]
```

**Before running or suggesting any `git commit`**, prompt the user:

1. **ai-assisted** — "Was this change AI-assisted? (yes/no)"

Use `[ai-assisted]` if yes, `[no-ai]` if no. Place the token at the end of the commit message, inside square brackets, as a standalone token on the same line.

**Examples:**

```bash
git commit -m "Add managing-stacks to TOC subnav [ai-assisted]"
git commit -m "Fix typo in concepts overview [no-ai]"
```

Do not omit the disclosure token. Do not add or require any other special format (no JIRA keys, no other suffixes) unless the user requests it.
